May 30 (Reuters) - Russian oil producer Rosneft (ROSN.MM) said on Monday that it would pay a record dividend of 41.66 roubles ($0.63) per share on its 2021 results, or 50% of its net profit. The board has recommended paying 23.63 roubles per share in a final dividend, having set its first-half dividend at 18.03 roubles per share. ($1 = 66.4000 roubles) Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.